1️⃣Complaints, accusations, whining, gossip.
The lower vibrations are destroying our inner strength. Learn to enjoy each day, thank the Universe, and it will return the favor. In addition, what we radiate, we receive

2️⃣ Activities that do not bring pleasure.
Unloving work, activities that bring you negativity and negative emotions. Communicating with unpleasant people also drains your energy

3️⃣ Communicating with toxic people. When we come in contact with people who are unpleasant, we lose energy. Toxic people feed on our energies. Ever notice that you feel tired after interacting with certain people.

4️⃣ The “me-too” syndrome. Many girls think no one can do it better than them. They used to pull everything on themselves, count only on their own strength and do not know how to ask and accept.

5️⃣ Competition with a man.
Modern girls want to assert themselves and prove to a man that they are as good as they can achieve and be realized, but this also burns energy. A woman should inspire, not lead to negative emotions. Leading and solving problems is not our job. Why would a man do anything for a girl if she can do everything herself.

6️⃣ Resentments.
Resentments and blocks prevent our energy from circulating properly. Resentment is a conscious choice and you condemn yourself to a life of negativity.

7️⃣ Lack of personal time.
No matter how hard and difficult it is, try to make time for yourself: reading, yoga, pilates, a massage or a warm bath - anything. Learn to slow down and live for your own pleasure, because chaos and bustle destroy a woman’s energy.

8️⃣ Lack of hobbies and creativity.
It is important for a woman to do something with her hands. If you create something beautiful you fill yourself with good mood and energy. You need to find an activity that will bring you pleaser. This can be drawing, dancing, embroidery, knitting or diamond embroidery.

9️⃣ Conflicts and arguments with men
Lack of communication with women
It is important for us to communicate with girlfriends and other girls. In this way, we are restored, filled with strength and relaxed.

Merry Orthodox Christmas🎄

I remember how I loved this holiday as a child and looked forward to it. Christmas in Moldova was celebrated for at least 3 days. In our house, we always had guests, the table was always filled with delicious homemade food prepared by my grandmother. I’m not even talking about the sweets🙊

I don’t remember many gifts, and it didn’t matter, the main thing was sweets.
I have very fond memories of celebrating Christmas, and to be honest, it's a pity that with age this holiday is left behind. 

Living in the USA, the focus is on local holidays and, of course, on December 25, Catholic Christmas (by the way, the photo in the carousel is from that day). 

In my home village, children are waiting for this holiday, so we have collected gifts and food for children and all those in need who we can help. 

We are a small volunteer team that cares about people from my home village.

I want to thank everyone who participated in this fundraising. 
We raised over $1000 and wow!  I am so happy!  I will keep you updated and share the report in a few days.

Mothers we have a chance to re-parent parts of oneself. 

Often mothers feel angry, lost, sad, incapable and incredibly triggered by their baby, which may mean they are having difficulty separating their own experience of childhood from their current reality. 

It’s so important for new mothers to understand this as they can find themselves feeling overwhelmed without knowing why, or can experience difficulty trusting themselves. 

Reacting unconsciously from a prior emotional wound or past memory can be a significant risk factor for mental health postpartum.

Amelia’s birth story or my second home birth experience ❤️

3 weeks ago around 12 am I felt my first wave 🌊 and I knew you are coming in that night. 

I downloaded the contraction app, called my midwife @midwifecammy after the 5th-7th contraction and told her that I’am probably in labour. 

I also called my friend and soul sister who was my doula @polina_fedko13 & let her know what’s happening. 

While my circle of women were gathering to support me I was feeling my waves and enjoying the beautiful time by myself while my husband and daughter were sleeping. I went to the bathtub and my waves became stronger and stronger. 

Around 1:30 am everyone came and I’m so blessed that everything was on the perfect time! 
Soon after around 2:30 am I went to the birth pool and in couple minutes our angel was born in the water.

I experienced the most beautiful and amazing birth from my dreams. I was truly manifesting exactly this experience. Less than 3 hours 😍

I will continue share and talk about my birth story and inspire other women. Because we must have a choice! We must choose the way we want to birth our kids and this must be normal and nothing to be scared or ashamed for.

I was judged when I chose to do home birth my first time 3 years ago. Even my family didn’t understand me, except my husband who is always by my side ❤️

I am so proud of myself and my decisions. When everyone is against your decision is super hard but I did not care. I always listen to myself. 

So this second time I even made a birth video which will come out soon😍 
I am here for those women who are afraid to be who they are and afraid of being judged and not understood. You are not alone! 

We must show how beautiful birth can be and how powerful we are! Let’s make the birth experience GREAT AGAIN! Aho🙏🏼
